      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the direct clinical QoI for CPB hemolysis assessment. Wall shear stress and exposure time are the mechanistic drivers of the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power law model employed. Validation QoIs are therefore directly relevant to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
