      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model input parameters identified; sensitivity analysis performed for parameters with significant uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for blood viscosity (±10%), inlet velocity profile (uniform vs. parabolic), and rotational speed (±50 RPM). NIH most sensitive to rotational speed (±7.2% NIH per ±50 RPM). Geometric tolerances propagated through five representative pump configurations spanning the design space."
